OL,7,FRicky Thomson, author of the report,
OL,8,Ftold journalists a "step change" is
OL,9,Fneeded in coming years as just over
OL,10,F2,050 wells are expected to be
OL,11,Fdecommissioned in the next decade `
OL,12,Fmore than 80% of active well stock.
OL,14,FComplicating the progress is the fact
OL,15,Fthat many of the ships and facilities
OL,16,Fused in oil and gas decommissioning
OL,17,Fare also needed for offshore wind
OL,18,Finstallation, with Mr Thomson saying
OL,19,Fthis creates a "direct clash" between
OL,20,Fthe two industries.
